.TH HSH 1 "2020-11-26" "Linux" "simple shell man page"
.SH NAME
.B hsh
- simple shell command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.b ./hsh
[
.I command_string
]
[
.I options
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a command line interpreter created as a project for Holberton School. Hsh is a simplified version of the standard Linux shell. The program was created and compiled on
.I Ubuntu 14.04 LTS
Using
.I GCC 4.8.4.
.SH OPTIONS

.B cd 
- change directory


.B env 
- print evironment

.B exit 
- exit the shell

.SH FILES

.B helper1 
- miscellaneous helper functions supporting program

.B Header_shell 
- header file

.B string_help2 
- contains function to parse tokens and other character array manipulation

.B string_help 
- contains functions to manipulate character arrays

.B prompt 
- main function to start shell

.B path_parser 
- contains function to parse the path values of a given environment variable

.SH EXAMPLE
 alexnsweet@rocketblaster.com:~/simple_shell$ ./hsh
 ($)
 ($)pwd
 /home/vagrant/simple_shell
 ($)exit
